25 March 2011The GCIS will host a two-day planning and strategic meeting, commonly referred to as the Government Communicators Forum (GCF) on the 28th and 29th March 2011.The GCF takes place quarterly and is attended by communicators from the three spheres of government. The March GCF marks the beginning of the financial year and sets the tone and agenda for government communications in a particular year.This year the meeting will focus on the pronouncements made by President Zuma in the 2011 State of the Nation Address with particular emphasis on job creation.Members of the media are invited to the GCF Gala Dinner as follows:Date: 28 March 2011 Venue: Gallagher Estate, Midrand, Gauteng Time: 18h00 for 18h30Mr Alastair Campbell, best known as the former British Prime Minister Tony Blair s spokesperson, will be the guest speaker at the Gala Dinner.RSVP with your name, mobile number and email address to: Bongiwe Gambu Cell: 082 714 9463 E-mail: bongiwe@gcis.gov.zaPlease note that only media who RSVP will be allowed access.For media enquiries contact: Neo Momodu Cell: 079 462 5081 Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)